Cloud mode uses fal's hosted API and FLUX.2 [klein] from Black Forest Labs:
https://fal.ai/models/fal-ai/flux-2/klein/realtime
https://github.com/black-forest-labs/flux2

FLUX.2 [klein] 4B model code and weights are published under Apache License 2.0.
Use of fal's hosted service is also subject to fal's separate terms.

The browser loads @fal-ai/client 1.10.1, distributed under the MIT License:
https://www.npmjs.com/package/@fal-ai/client/v/1.10.1

The optional local Mac mode integrates StreamDiffusion-Mac, an Apache-2.0
adaptation of StreamDiffusion:
https://github.com/patrickhartono/StreamDiffusion-Mac

SD-Turbo and TAESD weights are downloaded separately at runtime and retain
their respective licenses.

The visual direction was inspired by Ryan Stephen's public realtime diffusion
UI experiment. This is an independent implementation:
https://x.com/Ryan__Stephen/status/2066890410824528077
